Homa Bay Town MP Peter Kaluma has been charged in a Homa Bay court with assaulting his political opponent. He was accused of assaulting and injuring Washington Ogaga last Sunday during a rally in Homa Bay Stadium. The complainant is the state.Kaluma denied the charges before senior resident magistrate Paul Mayova. Kaluma&rsquo;s lawyer Samuel Nyauke urged the court to grant him affordable bail. The case will be heard on January 23 and 24.